6:
These fancy Yamato duds are really
on a whole other level, aren't they?
11: The fabrics look exquisite on you.
17:
I figured that when in Yamato, do as
the Yamato do, am I right?
21: But even more than the clothing...
27:
These people really know how to
ring in the new year with a bang!
30:
Grab your paddle! They're gonna
start the Hanetsuki tournament
without us!
32:
I'm gonna win the whole thing! Just
watch!
39:
Umm... Maybe it's a local racket
sport? The kimono shop lady gave
me a paddle as a freebie, and it's
just like that kid's.
42:
Who knows? If it seems fun, maybe
we could introduce it to Palpebra?
47:
Well, what are we waiting for? Let's
follow those kids and take a
look-see for ourselves!
52:
Whoa, check it out! Yep. I could
TOTALLY see something like this
catching on in Palpebra!
56:
Hmm... It looks like the game is to
prevent the feathered shuttlecock
from touching the ground.
59:
Boys and girls! Ladies and gents!
Grandpas and grandmas! We're
looking for contenders of all skill
levels and ages, and all are
welcome to enter!
60:
They say if a feather lands on you,
an entire year of good fortune
awaits! There's still time to sign up,
but act fast!
63:
I guess it's now or never if we wanna
try it out for ourselves, huh?
69: What do you say? Let's do this thing!
73:
Hard pass. I'm good with just
watching.
77:
I would only be a hindrance in my
current form, I imagine.
86:
Just Stella? What about the rest of
you guys?
93: I guess I'm still on the fence...
96:
The grand prize winner will be
treated to a fantastic, family-style,
five-star, five-course seafood feast!
100:
What the... Look at the size of that
snapper! And those jumbo shrimp
are actually jumbo-sized! Not to
mention the crabs and scallop...
*drool*
105:
Heh. Sounds like somebody wants a
shot at the grand prize.
114:
I mean, yes, but there's no way we'd
be able to win this thing without a
considerable amount of practice.
115:
Buuut... if we can come up with
some kind of plan or strategy, it
could be possible!
123:
That's the spirit, Alk! It's all about
attitude!
129:
If you think strategy's the key to
victory, it might be a good idea to
go after us.
134:
You're the most perceptive of our
bunch, Alk, so you could do some
reconnaisance first.
136:
Get a feel for the game, study our
opponents, and relay all that juicy
intel back to us. Sounds like a plan,
right?
139:
Though you'll need to be a silent
watcher. Our man on the inside, the
architect of this operation.
144:
All right. You might be
overestimating my spy potential
here, but I'll do whatever I can to
help!
149: Woohoo! Let's win this thing, gang!
158: I lost in the first round.
163:
A-at least you left your heart on the
field...
168:
On the bright side, thanks to
watching you play, I was able to get
a pretty good idea of how to
approach the shuttlecock!
172:
It actually falls a bit slower than
you'd expect, so it's easy to mess up
the timing.
174:
That being said, I don't think you
should have any trouble, Ellya,
especially given your track record
as the Starlight Sharpshooter.
177:
So I should use my speed to my
advantage, mixing up my pace to
throw off my opponent...
182:
Got it! I'll avenge you, Stella. Just
wait!
187:
Our five-star, five-course feast
depends on it!
192:
Don't you worry. I'm gonna win this
thing, free.
196:
Incredible. I can't even see the
shuttlecock anymore.
200:
This is pretty intense for a casual
tournament...
213: I won! I won, you guys!
218:
You played a splendid match out
there.
222:
I'll admit it... This ended up being
more entertaining than I thought.
225:
Sorry... maybe we'll have a shot at it
next time. Can you wait another
year?
229:
Hi there! I'd like to offer you a trade
of sorts, actually. Care to listen?
234:
Nothing tastes better than the taste
of victory, am I right? And look at
these portions!
237:
Thank you for inviting us. Are you
sure we're not party crashing?
240:
Of course! But remember your end
of the bargain—teach us all kinds of
stuff about Yamato, okay?
243:
A pretty sweet deal for both of us,
don't you think?
246:
She pulled that off quite expertly. By
framing it as an exchange, they'd be
more inclined to take the offer to
join us. Everyone wins.
250:
You think? I'm pretty sure she's just
on the hunt for ideas to bring back
to Palpebra.
256:
Cheers to the new year, everybody!
Bottoms up!
